import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='rate', kde=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the overall distribution of unemployment rates?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['rate'] = pd.to_numeric(data['rate'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['rate'])
    ax = sns.boxplot(x=data['rate'])
    ax.set(xlabel='Unemployment Rate')
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the average unemployment rate across the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean: {:.2f}'.format(data['rate'].mean()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
